  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Mix together gluten-free flour, cornmeal, and salt in a large bowl.",
    "Add melted coconut oil and water to the flour mixture, stirring until a dough forms.",
    "Roll out dough on a floured surface to a thickness of 1/8 inch.",
    "Fill the center of the dough with a shaggy mixture of sautéed peppers, onion, and garlic.",
    "Fold the dough over the filling and seal the edges by pressing with a fork.",
    "Place the pastry on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the filling is heated through."
